Kenya Power to Complete Pre-Paid Billing in 2016, Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-12-08T05:18:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/kenya-power-to-complete-pre-paid-billing-in-2016-daily-says.html
Kenya Power Ltd. (KPLL)  plans to shift all
its domestic customers to pre-paid billing in five years as part
of efforts to boost its  cash flow ,  Business Daily  reported,
citing Managing Director Joseph Njoroge.  The project will cost the company 10 billion shillings
($111 million), the Nairobi-based newspaper said. Kenya Power
presently has 1.4 million domestic consumers and has since 2009
installed 118,698 pre-paid meters, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at   eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  